subSubSection.paragraph:
Differential diagnosis. This species is similar to
Phyllocoptruta platycladusa
Xue, Song, Amrine & Hong 2007
, but can be differentiated from the latter by: the absence of a median line and submedian lines on the prodorsal shield (a short median line and relatively long submedian lines are present in
P. platycladusa
); having dorsal semiannuli with elliptical microtubercles on the wide, middorsal longitudinal furrow (dorsal semiannuli with microtubercles laterally in
P. platycladusa
); coxal plates I with short lines, coxal plates II with granules (coxal plates I are smooth and coxal plates II have short lines in
P. platycladusa
).
